libqtcad - BRL-CAD Qt widget library
=====================================

`libqtcad` is the shared library of reusable Qt widgets, models, and helper
classes used to build BRL-CAD's Qt-based applications (currently `qged`, and
indirectly `archer`).  Public headers live in `include/qtcad/`, implementations
in `src/libqtcad/`.

This README is a navigational overview.  Per-class API documentation belongs in
the public headers themselves.

Library taxonomy
----------------

The contents of libqtcad fall into a small number of categories.  When adding a
new file, place it in the category that best matches its responsibility.

* Canvas / display-manager widgets
    `QgGL`        - QOpenGLWidget-backed canvas driving dm-qtgl
    `QgSW`        - QWidget-backed canvas driving dm-swrast (software raster)
    `QgView`      - thin wrapper that picks one of the canvas types at runtime
    `QgQuadView`  - 4-up arrangement of `QgView`s

* Tree / data models for .g database content
    `QgModel`               - QAbstractItemModel over a .g hierarchy
    `QgItem`                - per-tree-node payload used by `QgModel`
    `QgTreeView`            - QTreeView subclass that knows how to paint
                              `QgModel` rows
    `QgTreeSelectionModel`  - selection model paired with `QgTreeView`
    `QgAttributesModel`     - model exposing one object's attribute AVS
    `QgKeyVal*`             - generic key/value tree model + delegate + view
    `QgUtil`                - free functions returning per-object icons and
                              the comb-type classification used for those icons

* Mouse-event filters installed on a view to implement editing modes
    `QgPolyFilter`     (+ five derived classes for create/update/select/point/move)
    `QgSelectFilter`   (+ point / box / ray)
    `QgMeasureFilter`  (+ 2D / 3D)
    `QgSketchFilter`   (+ several sketch-edit derivations)

* General-purpose Qt widgets
    `QgAccordion`       - vertical stack of collapsing panels
    `QgToolPalette`     - palette of icon-buttons that toggle docked control
                          widgets (`QgToolPaletteElement` / `QgToolPaletteButton`)
    `QgFlowLayout`      - flow layout (from Qt examples; BSD-licensed)
    `QgColorRGB`        - color picker combining a swatch button with text entry
    `QgDockWidget`      - QDockWidget with extra "promote to top-level window"
                          behavior
    `QgConsole`         - QPlainTextEdit-based interactive console
                          (ParaView-derived); used as the GED command prompt
    `QgConsoleListener` - QThread-backed FD reader feeding `QgConsole`
                          (juangburgos/QConsoleListener-derived; MIT-licensed)
    `QgAppExecDialog`   - dialog that runs a child process and displays its
                          stdout / stderr stream in a `QgConsole`
    `QgViewCtrl`        - QToolBar with rotate / translate / scale / center /
                          raytrace / framebuffer toggle actions

* Dialogs / format converters
    `QgGeomImport`         - chooses a .g file to open, running any required
                              converter
    `ASCImportDialog`, `RhinoImportDialog`, `STEPImportDialog`
                           - format-specific configuration dialogs invoked by
                              `QgGeomImport`

* Cross-cutting helpers
    `defines.h`         - `QTCAD_EXPORT` macro and env-driven slot/event
                          tracing macros (`QTCAD_SLOT`, `QTCAD_EVENT`)
    `QgSignalFlags.h`   - bitmask flags passed through view-update signals
    `bindings.{h,cpp}`  - shared key / mouse / wheel event handlers used by
                          the canvas widgets (private to libqtcad)
    `qtcad_resources.qrc` - icon resources

Signal / slot conventions
-------------------------

The conventions documented in `QgSignalFlags.h` apply throughout the library.
Briefly:

1. The application provides a single `view_update(flags)` signal that fans out
   to every widget which may need to refresh.
2. Widgets emit a `view_changed(flags)` signal when something they do may
   affect the view.  Applications connect that to a `do_view_changed` slot
   that turns around and re-emits `view_update`.
3. Widgets provide a `do_view_update(flags)` slot, connected by the
   application to `view_update`, which performs the widget-local refresh.
   `do_view_update` MUST NOT itself emit (directly or transitively)
   `view_changed`, to avoid loops.

The `flags` parameter is currently a bitmask of the `QG_VIEW_*` `#define`s in
`QgSignalFlags.h`.  A future cleanup will replace it with a `Q_FLAG`-decorated
`enum class`.

Threading model
---------------

The library is single-threaded in the Qt-main-thread sense, with one
exception: `QgConsoleListener` runs an `m_thread` that watches a file
descriptor and emits text lines via a queued connection back to the main
thread.  All other widgets, models, and filters expect to be created, used,
and destroyed on the Qt GUI thread.

Lifetime / ownership
--------------------

QWidgets follow the normal Qt parent/child ownership rules.  `QgView` owns its
canvas widget (`QgSW` or `QgGL`); the canvas in turn allocates and owns its
local `struct bview` (`local_v`).  Filters installed via
`QgView::add_event_filter` are owned by the caller, not the view.

Consumers
---------

Inside the BRL-CAD tree libqtcad is consumed by:

* `src/qged` and its plugins (the primary client)
* `src/libqtcad/tests` (`qgmodel`, `qgview`, `qsketch`, plus GED-level tests
  that exercise the dm backends end-to-end)

`archer` and `libtclcad` do not currently depend on libqtcad.

Modernization plan
------------------

The library is the subject of a longer-running modernization effort tracked
in the project plan that originally introduced this README.  Subsequent PRs
will progressively:

* tighten encapsulation (move public data behind accessors; adopt the pimpl
  idiom for the heaviest classes)
* unify the `QgGL` / `QgSW` duplication behind a common `QgCanvasBase`
* unify the polygon / select / measure / sketch filter hierarchies behind a
  common `QgViewFilter` base
* replace the `unsigned long long` view-flag signals with a `Q_FLAG`
  `enum class`
* introduce a `QgSession` abstraction so the models no longer talk directly
  to `struct ged` / `struct db_i`
* wrap the public API in a `qtcad::` namespace
* expand the test suite to use `QSignalSpy` / `QAbstractItemModelTester`

Each phase is intended to land independently while keeping `libqtcad`,
`qged`, `archer`, `dm-qtgl`, and `dm-swrast` building.
